{"tid":843985,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"中國領事館要求主辦組織向打人女道歉！","createTime":"2018-10-01T13:57:05.000Z","updateTime":"2018-10-01T14:13:05.000Z","uid":47714,"like":0,"dislike":5,"uniUserReply":8,"replies":[{"pid":"fbbdf1e9ad4d297329f5451d656fffe8aee272d4","tid":843985,"uid":47714,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-01T13:57:05.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/HKCPForum/posts/2485886678096151\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FHKCPForum%2Fposts%2F2485886678096151&d=bhgyCO6mn7isTI%2FN8FzTogHZiNw4JStbf0cW9gpNrZc%3D&h=891cf502\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/HKCPForum/posts/2485886678096151</a><br />\n<br />\n中國領事館要求主辦組織向打人女道歉！<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/1457138397739962/posts/1825496430904155/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2F1457138397739962%2Fposts%2F1825496430904155%2F&d=bhgyCO6mn7isTI%2FN8FzTogHZiNw4JStbf0cW9gpNrZc%3D&h=490be743\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/1457138397739962/posts/1825496430904155/</a><br />\n<br />\nSubsequently the Chinese Embassy issued a statement which called on the organisers of the fringe event to &ldquo;apologise to the Chinese journalist&rdquo; for &ldquo;obstruction&rdquo; and &ldquo;assault&rdquo; at the fringe event. The Embassy said: &ldquo;Hong Kong is China's Hong Kong. Hong Kong affairs are purely China's domestic affairs. The fringe event of the Human Rights Committee of UK Conservative Party during the Party's annual conference boosted the arrogance of the anti-China separatists. It was a cause for grave concern and strong objection. China firmly opposes interference in Hong Kong's internal affairs by anyone or any organization in any form.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nChinese Embassy Statement:<br />\n<a href=\"https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d774d3259544e7a457a6333566d54/share_p.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.cgtn.com%2Fnews%2F3d3d774d3259544e7a457a6333566d54%2Fshare_p.html&d=bhgyCO6mn7isTI%2FN8FzTogHZiNw4JStbf0cW9gpNrZc%3D&h=b963d4a8\" target=\"_blank\">https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d774d3259544e7a457a6333566d54/share_p.html</a><br />\n<br />\nBenedict Rogers, Chair of Hong Kong Watch said: &ldquo;Video footage of the event exposes how absurd this statement is. Over 80 witnesses in the room saw that the Chinese journalist slapped our volunteer twice, and the video shows her hitting him again. She should apologise immediately and the Chinese government should retract their statement. At a party conference in the UK we have every right to discuss Hong Kong, not least because Britain has legal obligations to the people of Hong Kong under the Sino-British Joint Declaration. Under this treaty, lodged at the United Nations, Hong Kong affairs are still very much Britain&rsquo;s concern.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.hongkongwatch.org/all-posts/2018/10/1/volunteer-assaulted-a-conservative-party-conference-fringe-event-on-human-rights-in-hong-kong\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hongkongwatch.org%2Fall-posts%2F2018%2F10%2F1%2Fvolunteer-assaulted-a-conservative-party-conference-fringe-event-on-human-rights-in-hong-kong&d=bhgyCO6mn7isTI%2FN8FzTogHZiNw4JStbf0cW9gpNrZc%3D&h=adfa12f4\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.hongkongwatch.org/all-posts/2018/10/1/volunteer-assaulted-a-conservative-party-conference-fringe-event-on-human-rights-in-hong-kong</a><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://static1.squarespace.com/static/58ecfa82e3df284d3a13dd41/t/5bb1f15a0d929713f2acadb8/1538388353894/Journo.png?format=500w\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic1.squarespace.com%2Fstatic%2F58ecfa82e3df284d3a13dd41%2Ft%2F5bb1f15a0d929713f2acadb8%2F1538388353894%2FJourno.png%3Fformat%3D500w&h=c61e40a7&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"dba45f8ddb5e96964dd35ff6d5860da5b535d78b","tid":843985,"uid":38194,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-01T14:03: